chatNodeSystemPromptTip:
Fixed prompts can guide the model's conversation direction when adjusted. They will be fixed at the beginning of the context.
Variables like {{language}} can be used. If a knowledge base is linked, you can guide the model on when to search the knowledge base through appropriate descriptions.
For example: 
You are an assistant for the movie 'Interstellar'. When users inquire about content related to 'Interstellar', please search the knowledge base and incorporate the search results into your response.
The above content should be retained in its format.
userGuideTip: You can set up a guide before the conversation, configure global variables, and provide next steps guidance.
variableTip:
Before starting the conversation, you can request users to provide some content as specific variables for this dialogue round. This module comes after the welcome text. 
Variables can be injected into other modules as string inputs in the form of {{variable key}}, for example: prompts, qualifiers, etc.
welcomeTextTip:
Send an initial content before each conversation. Supports standard Markdown syntax. Additional tags available:
[Shortcut Key]: Users can click to directly send this question.
questionGuideTip: After the conversation ends, generate three guiding questions.
ttsTip: When enabled, TTS feature can be used after each conversation. Using this feature may incur additional charges.

userChatInputIntro: The flow will start executing from this module when a user sends a message.
simpleChatIntro: A very simple AI application that you can bind to a knowledge base or tool.
VariableTypeParagraphTip: Allow users to input up to 4000 characters in the dialogue box.
VariableTypeApiTip: You can pass variables through API endpoints or shared link queries. The main purpose of introducing this variable type is for variable prompts.
AI response switch tip: If you want the current node to not output content, you can turn off this switch. The AI output will not be displayed to the user, and you can manually use 'AI reply content' for special handling.
AI support tool tip: The model that supports function calls can better use tool calls.
Assigned reply intro: This module can directly reply with a specified content. It is often used for guidance or prompts. When non-string content is passed in, it will be converted to a string for output.
Chat entrance intro: When the user sends a message, the process will start executing from this module.
Classify question intro:
Determine the type of question based on the user's history and the current question. Multiple question types can be added. Here is a template example:
Type 1: Greeting
Type 2: Questions about product 'usage'
Type 3: Questions about product 'purchase'
Type 4: Other questions
Dataset search intro: Call the dataset search capability to find content that may be related to the question.
Dataset search result concat intro: Multiple dataset search results can be merged and output. The final sorting output is performed using the RRF merging method.
Extract field intro: Data can be extracted from the text, such as SQL statements, search keywords, code, etc.
Http request intro: An HTTP request can be made to perform more complex operations (network search, database query, etc.).
Query extension intro: Using the query optimization function can improve the accuracy of continuous dataset searches. After using this function, AI will first construct one or more new search terms based on the context, which are more conducive to dataset search. This module is built into the dataset search module. If you only perform one dataset search, you can directly use the built-in completion function of the dataset.
Running app intro: You can choose to call another application.
TFSwitch intro: True False output based on the input content. By default, when the input content is false, undefined, null, 0, or none, it will output false. You can also add some custom strings to supplement the false output content. Non-character, non-numeric, non-boolean types directly output True.
textEditor intro: Can process and output fixed or input text. Non-string type data will eventually be converted to string type.
Response content help:
You can use \n to achieve continuous line breaks.
You can achieve replies through external module input, and external module input will override the currently filled content.
If non-string type data is passed in, it will be automatically converted to a string.
Classify background:
For example: 
1. AIGC (Artificial Intelligence Generated Content) refers to the use of artificial intelligence technology to automatically or semi-automatically generate digital content, such as text, images, music, videos, etc.
2. AIGC technology includes but is not limited to natural language processing, computer vision, machine learning, and deep learning. These technologies can create new content or modify existing content to meet specific creative, educational, entertainment, or informational needs.

questionGuideTemplate: You are an AI intelligent assistant, capable of answering and solving my questions. Based on the previous conversation, help me generate 3 questions to guide me to continue asking. The length of the questions should be less than 20 characters, separated by commas, and returned in JSON array format, e.g., ["Question 1","Question 2","Question 3"]. Use UTF-8 encoding, avoid generating loops, avoid generating extra KEYS and VALUES, only need the simplest array form with three values.
